    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/923</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-22">March 22,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Italian Ambassador called and inquired whether there were any other phases or
                    features relating to the United States-Japanese affairs outside of what was
                    revealed in the two notes recently exchanged between the Foreign Minister of
                    Japan and myself,<note n="11" xml:id="d543fn11">For text of message handed to
                        the Secretary of State on February 21, 1934, and the Secretary’s reply,
                        handed to the Japanese Ambassador on March 3, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_127">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 127</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_128">128</ref>.</note> to which I replied that
                    nothing had been said or done or suggested relative to any important phase of
                    the relations between the two countries outside of what was contained in the two
                    notes themselves. He made inquiry about our attitude toward the recognition of
                    Manchukuo, to which I replied that there is nothing new to be said by me on that
                        subject.<note n="12" xml:id="d543fn12">A similar Belgian inquiry was made
                        the same day (711.94/924).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
